population: Bajra field Rajasthan is a mineral-rich state and has a diversified economy having agriculture, mining and tourism as its main engines of growth.  The state mines produce gold, silver, sandstone, limestone, marble, rock phosphate, copper and lignite. It is the second-largest producer of cement and contributes one tenth of the salt produced in India
